# README Rules

## Badges

Use [shields.io](https://shields.io) style. Place badges right below the title.

- Prefer: build/CI, tests, license, version (e.g. npm), language/framework.
- Format: `![alt](https://img.shields.io/...)`

## Structure

Recommended heading order:

1. Title (`#` only)
2. Badges
3. Overview (1–2 sentences)
4. Table of contents (optional, for long READMEs)
5. Setup / Installation
6. Usage
7. Other (API, config, contributing, etc.)
8. License

## Title & overview

- Single `#` for the project name.
- Overview: short, clear; what it does and who it’s for.

## Setup / Installation

- Use numbered steps.
- State prerequisites (e.g. Node version, OS) when relevant.

## Usage

- Show minimal working example.
- Link to full docs if needed.

## Code blocks

- Always set the language: ` ```bash `, ` ```ts `, ` ```json `, etc.

## License

- State license name or link to a LICENSE file.
